article.description: Jackson St. picks up win at Evansville 57-51
article.headline: Jackson St. picks up win at Evansville 57-51
article.linkText: Jackson St. picks up win at Evansville 57-51
article.story: EVANSVILLE, Ind. -- Brandon West scored 14 points and grabbed 22 rebounds to lead Jackson State to a 57-51 win over Evansville on Saturday. Julysses Nobles also had 14 points for the Tigers (3-7) with Marcus Love adding 11 off the bench. Egidijus Mockevicius led the Aces (6-5) with 16 points and D.J. Balentine had 12. A big key for the Tigers was holding Balentine down. Balentine entered the game as the 4th leading scorer in the nation at 23.9 points a game. And the defense was not just focused on one player as Evansville was held to 25 below its average and the 34 percent shooting, 15 percent below average. West helped the Tigers pull out the win. After a Marcus Love free throw put Jackson State ahead 54-50 at 47 seconds, West grabbed a defensive rebound, followed by an offensive rebound and tip-in at 22 seconds to make it 56-50.
